Based on the provided code, the issue might be related to how the `page` prop is being handled in the `Home` component. In the condition you have:

```js
if(page === null && page === undefined) {
    return null;
}
```

This condition will never evaluate to `true` because `page` can't be both `null` and `undefined` at the same time. Instead, you should use the logical OR operator (`||`) to check if `page` is either `null` or `undefined`:

```js
if (page === null || page === undefined) {
    return null;
}
```

This way, if `page` is either `null` or `undefined`, the `Home` component will return `null`, and nothing will be rendered.

If you still encounter issues, it might be helpful to log the `context.req.headers` in the `getServerSideProps` function to debug the incoming request headers and verify if the values are being parsed correctly.

